nzie District Métis, his determination to take peoples experience seriously, not metaphorically, and his thinking about social organization and kinship. Contributors include Sam Ajzenstat, Michael Asch, David J. Damas , Harvey A. Feig, Kenneth Little, Antonia Mills, Richard J. Preston, Mary Black Rogers, and Robert Wishar. An unpublished paper about a 1930s caribou hunt in which he participated finishes the collection, giving Dick the last word.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAnthropologistszCanadavBiography. 0aEthnologyzCanada, Northern. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aEthnography. 4aSocial Science: Anthropology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aAjzenstat, Sam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAsch, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlack-Rogers, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDamas, David J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFeit, Harvey A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLittle, Kenneth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMills, Antonia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPreston, Richard J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPreston, Richard J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSlobodin, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWishart, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi